title: Primer sets of a revealing graphic, personal history of Western Painting using the complete and basic iambus throughout. Eighty pieces, ten each set of eight: Marster Buckt Tho Nitid / Makar Vanisht Oyez Fúnnee
medium: Wood strainers, canvas, paper, carbon paper, waxed paper, tracing paper, linen, acetate sheets, sandpaper, glass, cheesecloth, sand, synthetic leather, silk, masking  tape, tape, thread, paintbrush bristles, marker and pencil
dimensions: 72 pieces ranging from 16 × 16” (40.6 × 40.6 cm) to 16 × 20” (40.6 × 50.8 cm), overall dimensions variable
